<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Catapult ships unsandboxed because it needs to:
        - write into a user-chosen download folder anywhere on disk
        - spawn yt-dlp and ffmpeg as child processes
        - read the user's browser cookies (Safari/Chrome/Firefox)
        Each is incompatible with the App Sandbox without elaborate
        temporary-exception entitlements that wouldn't survive notarization.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <false/>

    <!--
        Hardened-runtime exceptions that PREVIOUS versions of this file
        granted are deliberately omitted now:

          - allow-jit                         (Catapult never JIT-compiles)
          - allow-unsigned-executable-memory  (no mprotect+exec at runtime)
          - disable-library-validation        (we want library validation ON)
          - allow-dyld-environment-variables  (no DYLD_* overrides needed)

        yt-dlp / ffmpeg run as separate child processes with their own
        signatures and entitlements; the parent app doesn't need to relax
        its own runtime to launch them. Tightening these closes off
        memory-corruption-to-RCE primitives and keeps the surface small.
    -->

    <!--
        Outbound HTTP only — for yt-dlp/ffmpeg installer downloads,
        SponsorBlock + YouTube RSS feeds, and Sparkle's appcast.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
